		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Can someone test games on real GB hardware?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think the flickering in <em>Batman</em> and <em>Serpent</em> is an intentional translucency effect, if <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=192995#p192995" class="postlink">ccovell's comment</a> is to be believed. It wasn't noticeable on the original Game Boy because the LCD was so slow. Have you tried enabling frame averaging (also called motion blur) in these emulators to simulate a slow LCD?<br /><br />I have a working Game Boy Color, tested with <em>Space Invaders</em> two days ago, but a copy of <em>Serpent</em> on eBay would cost about $12.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


